---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
	<main class="content">
		<article class="panel bulletin-article">
			<div class="dispatch-tag">[TECHNICAL BULLETIN 02]</div>
			<h1>The Theology of the Wrench</h1>
			
			<section class="bulletin-content lede">
				<p>Sentimental prayer is ungrounded energy. Mechanical realignment is the physical act of repair as liturgy.</p>
			</section>

			<section class="bulletin-body">
				<h2>The Friction of Sentimental Prayer</h2>
				<p>Most modern orientation systems (faith-based or secular) rely on "sentimental energy." This is the belief that internal emotional states can override external structural failures. It is ungrounded. It is high-voltage energy with no path to the earth.</p>
				<p>Trying to solve a structural rot in your life through sentiment is like trying to fix a faulty breaker by wishing the lights back on. The machine does not care about your feelings; it cares about the circuit.</p>

				<h2>Mechanical Realignment</h2>
				<p>We propose a shift to the **Theology of the Wrench**. In this framework, the act of repair—the physical tightening of a bolt, the leveling of a foundation—is the highest form of liturgical participation. It is the recognition that matter precedes hierarchy.</p>
				<p>To fix the engine, you must apply the wrench. You must understand the torque specifications. You must handle the metal. This is not "spiritual advice"; it is structural maintenance.</p>
			</section>

			<section class="hard-stop">
				<p>If the chassis is seizing, the sentiment is irrelevant. You need the schematic.</p>
			</section>

			<div class="cta-row audit-cta">
				<h2>[ACTION REQUIRED]</h2>
				<p>Stop operating on superstition. Secure the 30-Day Structural Audit and begin the mechanical realignment of your life.</p>
				<a class="btn primary highlight" href="https://buy.stripe.com/dRmbIT2Z26pAbPPf7ZbV600" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GET THE AUDIT - $12.00</a>
			</div>
		</article>
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	.bulletin-article {
		border: 2px solid var(--accent);
		padding: 3rem 2rem;
	}
	.bulletin-body h2 {
		margin-top: 2rem;
		border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
		padding-left: 1rem;
	}
	.audit-cta {
		margin-top: 4rem;
		padding: 2rem;
		background: rgba(178, 71, 45, 0.05);
		border: 1px solid var(--accent);
		border-radius: 12px;
		text-align: center;
	}
</style>
